## Avoid

- Module-level database connections or HTTP clients that are recreated on every
  rerun.
- Calling `st.rerun()` inside loops or callbacks that immediately trigger the
  same condition again.
- Mixing callback wiring with business logic inside widget callbacks.
- Mutable default arguments in cached functions.
- Calling `st.write()`, `st.dataframe()`, or other render functions inside a
  cached function.
